•	Developed a Single Inductor Multi-Port DC-DC Converter integrating solar PV and battery sources for efficient electric vehicle (EV) power management.

•	Designed to deliver dual regulated outputs for motor drive and auxiliary loads, enhancing power flexibility and energy utilization.

•	Implemented and tested using MATLAB/Simulink, verifying stable operation, voltage regulation, and balanced current distribution.

•	Adopted a compact single-inductor topology to minimize hardware components, reduce losses, and simplify control design.

•	Demonstrated efficient hybrid energy conversion, supporting sustainable and cost-effective electric vehicle architectures.
